description.narrative: (Zimbabwe): .With FY 2016 funds, USAID/Zimbabwe's Improving Family Planning Service project will continue to train and maintain nine clinical outreach teams and a social franchise network of 50 private medical service providers to: conduct awareness campaigns and increase the population's knowledge of modern Family Planning (FP) methods and FP service availability; conduct outreach services and deliver FP methods of choice to 140,000 men and women; and provide FP social franchise services to 70,000 men and women in rural, peri-urban, and urban areas in three provinces. These services are expected to avert 114,000 unintended pregnancies and 290 maternal deaths......
